Interestingly, since you've not specified any grouping, you're using a shuffle grouping which *should* distribute things between the two downstream components pretty evenly.  We're using shuffle groupings all over the place and seeing a pretty even load distribution.  The only time we've seen that not be the case is when some tuples take a lot longer to process than others, but that doesn't seem to be the case from your screenshot.

