Ok, I'm loving this interface experiment. It rethinks how we've been doing `displayOrder` and `transforms` for mimebundle outputs.

Play with it now via https://nteract-components-yizfzoaduc.now.sh/#!/ExecuteResult

As a preview, you declare which components you'll render with as children, in order of decreasing priority:

```
<ExecuteResult
  data={{
    "text/plain": "plain was richer",
    "text/html": "<b>HTML was richer</b>"
  }}
>
  <HTML />
  <Plain />
</ExecuteResult>;
```

Any props that get passed in to these children get passed on through when rendered so you can pass in custom things:

```
<ExecuteResult
  data={{
    "text/plain": "plain was richer",
    "text/html": "<b>HTML was richer</b>"
  }}
>
  <HTML iframeMe="yesplease" />
  <Plain />
</ExecuteResult>;
```

🎉 

In terms of how our current interface works, we can adapt old code like this:

```
<ExecuteResult
  data={{
    "text/plain": "plain was richer",
    "text/html": "<b>HTML was richer</b>"
  }}
>
  {displayOrder.map(mimetype => transforms[mimetype])}
</ExecuteResult>
```

